\section{Problem 5}
For an ideal gas, the partition function is $Z=\frac{1}{N!}\left(\frac{V}{\lambda ^3} \right)^N$.
We can then find the Helmholtz free energy:
\begin{gather}
 A=-kT\ln{Z}\\
 \ln{Z}=N\left(\ln{V}-\ln{\lambda ^3}\right)-N\ln{N}-N\\
 \ln{Z}=N\left(\ln{\frac{Ve}{N}}-\ln{\lambda ^3}\right)\\
 A=-Nkt\left(\ln{\frac{Ve}{N}}-\ln{\lambda ^3}\right)
\end{gather}


